<item>
            <title>[AMQ-5423] STOMP protocol converter tracks pending ACKS but doesn&apos;t remove the state once ACK&apos;d</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-5423</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The STOMP protocol converter tracks pending acks in order to suppress duplicate acks but it fails to properly clean up the state data once and ACK, NACK to TX completion event happens.  This results in a memory leak. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12753151">AMQ-5423</key>
